node.text: Following on from my support of @mindcharity through the @leytonorientfc partnership I’m proud to be supporting #MentalHealthMinute with @heads_together and @radiocentre_uk. Whoever you are, and whatever you’re going through, it’s important that you remember you’re not alone. #MentalHealthAwarenessWeek

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Harry Kane on September 19, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, beard, people sitting and indoor.

node.text: RIP Jimmy Greaves. A true legend and one of the great goalscorers. Thoughts are with his family and friends.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Harry Kane on September 16, 2021 tagging @lucasmoura7, and @spursofficial. May be an image of 2 people.

node.text: Very proud to have made the most European appearances in @spursofficial club history. Tough game and loads to improve on for the weekend.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Harry Kane on September 10, 2021 tagging @soccersupplement. May be an image of 1 person, playing football and grass.

node.text: Good three games with @england, now ready for the @premierleague. @soccersupplement got me covered. #UpYourGame

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Harry Kane on September 08, 2021 tagging @harrymaguire93, and @england. May be an image of 2 people and stadium.

node.text: Gutted not to see out the win tonight. Loads of positives from these three games and a huge step closer to World Cup qualification. 🦁🦁🦁

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Harry Kane on September 07, 2021 tagging @england. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text: Big push to make it three from three this international break 💪🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Harry Kane in Wembley Stadium with @england. May be an image of playing a sport.

node.text: Got the job done. Another step closer to the World Cup 💪🦁🦁🦁

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Harry Kane on September 02, 2021 tagging @england. May be an image of 1 person, playing football and grass.

node.text: Brilliant win in front of a hostile crowd. Kept our composure well to make it four from four. Back to Wembley to try and keep the run going 🦁🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Harry Kane on September 01, 2021 tagging @sanchooo10, @trentarnold66, and @england. May be an image of 2 people and people standing.

node.text: World Cup qualifiers. We’re ready to go. 💪🦁🦁🦁

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Harry Kane on August 31, 2021 tagging @england. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text: Amazing to meet up with the @england squad and see some of the incredible messages we have received over the summer. Thank you 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿🙏

node.text: Three out of three. Great start before the international break👌
